<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4547862>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 7. A–D: Amphicarpa duploplicata. A: dissected individual 11 mm in height; B: undissected body inside opened tunic revealing short stolon at posterior end of body; C: opened branchial sac stained with haemalum showing two longitudinal folds per side, with a very short partial fold on ventral right side (on the left in photo), e=endostyle; D: enlarged view of portion of branchial sac showing parastigmatic vessels. E, F: Eusynstyela hartmeyeri. E: whole colony 6 cm in width; F: enlarged view of four zooids each 6–7 mm in width." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4547862/files/figure.png" .

